The paper deals with distributed parameter estimation in multi-agent networks with wireless communication links, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on wireless channel impairments and equalization coefficients indicates that it is likely to be in the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of diffusion algorithms and dynamic adaptation also suggests that it could be in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) categories. Finally, the application of these techniques to parameter estimation implies that it could be relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as well.
